@{PARD}
@{B}Shocker Habitat/Society:@{UB}@{PAR}

Shockers are not natives of the prime material planes, but can be found
wandering in any climate or terrain (though they dislike rain), usually near
civilization. They normally use their shape-change ability to fit into their
surroundings. Shockers often take an interest in the affairs of humans and
demihumans and they seem to take pleasure in antagonizing them in any way they
can. There are many speculations as to the reason for this type of behavior, but
no one knows their true motives. For some reason, they seem to ignore dwarves
and gnomes.@{PAR}

Not much is known of the origin, behavior, or social structure of these
creatures. It is thought that they are composed of pure energy, but this is only
speculation.@{PAR}

@ENDNODE

