@{PARD}
@{B}Shocker Ecology:@{UB}@{PAR}

There is a 2% chance that a conjure air elemental spell, staff, or similar
device will summon a shocker instead of an air elemental. Shockers encountered
in this manner will be in their natural form 95%of the time. The summoner has
only a 5% chance per level over 6 of successfully controlling a shocker
conjurered in this manner (to a maximum of 90%. Also, there is a 10% chance per
round that control will be lost, in which case the shocker will immediately
attack the summoner and his or her party. Devices which control or protect
against normal elementals do not work on shockers; dismissal, banishment, and
similar spells and devices have a 20% chance of failing even if the shocker
fails its magic resistance roll and saving throws.@{PAR}

It is rumored that magics exist that will summon and/or control a shocker
directly; these are said to give results similar to the more common elemental-
related devices.@{PAR}

